{
  "texts": [
    "Validation of a model against a historical dataset (such as those added to The Transparency Project) may hold little weight when evaluating contemporary performance.",
    "As such, ML benchmarks for gambling cannot be static.",
    "Government mandates that require data sharing (see Newall and Swanton, 2024) are likely to be the most successful way of accessing periodically updated datasets for a benchmarking suite.",
    "Regardless, successfully sharing and deploying the first iteration of benchmarking datasets without compromising privacy will be essential to building trust with operators and the public alike, and ensuring continuous buy-in from industry stakeholders.",
    "Technology, specifically AI and its subsets such as ML, are being increasingly used to support industry efforts to minimize harms."
  ]
}